This course is for supporting student's professional development by creating continuous opportunities to associate studies of domain- and subject-didactics with teacher's activities in an educational institution. As a result of continuous reflection the course creates opportunities to analyse and therefore to give an adequate evaluation to his/her knowledge, skills, attitudes and needs for professional development concerning domain- and subject-specific competence and didactics.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course has two main goals that should be achieved jointly with the domain- and subject-didactics courses and pedagogical practice: 1)	to support student's improvement to be a teacher by creating opportunities to associate studies of subject, domain- and subject-didactics with teacher's activities in an educational institution; 2)	to give a student an opportunity to perform traineeship tasks in Religious Education in different educational institutions, on different levels of an education institution and with students of special educational needs.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1)	is able to plan teaching process in Religious Education, to teach and to analyze class or educational activity taking into account learners' speciality, prior knowledge, needs and interests; 2)	is able to analyze based on his/her experience his/her competence, skills and needs related to the subject of religious Education or domain of social sciences  in order to plan his/her further actions for professional development; 3)	notices educational special needs related to subject or domain and is able to look for possibilities to solve them.
